description:
Next, we learn about Nicolas Ridley and Hugh Latimer, who had a powerful impact on the shaping of Protestant Britain. During the reign of Mary Tudor, over 260 Protestants were put to death in England, earning her the title, 'Bloody Mary.' The most high-profile group were the Oxford Martyrs, and the first two of these to be killed were Hugh Latimer and Nicholas Ridley. Their refusal to back down on what some might say was an insignificant issue, cost them both their lives.
